@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Car Dealership App";
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4">Welcome to the Car Dealership App</h1>
    <p>This app is a made to reassemble car dealership management system. It includes a database for managing cars in the dealership.</p>
    <p>To access the admin features, use the following credentials:</p>
    <p>Email: admin@gmail.com</p>
    <p>Password: <span id="password">***************</span> <button onclick="revealPassword()">Show</button></p>
    <p>The admin user can edit, delete, and insert cars, as well as view details about existing ones. Additionally, the admin can filter cars by searching for their manufacturer (by make).</p>
</div>

<script>
    function revealPassword() {
        var passwordField = document.getElementById("password");
        passwordField.innerText = "Car123456789*";
    }
</script>
